15:37.560 --> 15:38.560
Poor kid.

15:38.960 --> 15:40.280
Wife weren't that happy.

15:40.360 --> 15:42.560
I know, he's having a breakdown, in't he?

15:42.640 --> 15:44.840
-You think?
-What do you mean?

15:44.920 --> 15:46.960
Well, you don't believe he's just trans?

15:47.440 --> 15:50.040
I dunno. As I say, I'm old.

15:50.720 --> 15:54.840
-He could be trans <i>and </i>having a breakdown.
-Yeah. Anything's possible these days.

15:55.800 --> 15:59.120
-Do you still get transvestites?
-What do you mean?

15:59.520 --> 16:04.000
Well... now, people are transgender,
ain't they, or gender fluid?

16:04.080 --> 16:08.400
So, a bloke can say,
"I identify as a bloke or a woman,"

16:08.480 --> 16:10.920
and that's their gender,
whatever they say it is.

16:11.000 --> 16:12.960
-Right.
-Well, years ago,

16:13.040 --> 16:14.680
you used to have transsexuals,

16:14.760 --> 16:17.480
where you'd have an operation
to become a proper bird.

16:17.560 --> 16:19.560
And you had transvestites,

16:19.640 --> 16:22.800
you know, blokes that liked
to dress up as a bird now and again.

16:22.880 --> 16:25.840
You don't really see them ones anymore.

16:25.920 --> 16:27.720
But they were like that fella.

16:28.160 --> 16:31.760
They didn't do all of the,
"I identify as a real woman," or anything.

16:32.360 --> 16:35.120
Then you had, like,
young people being a bit androgynous,

16:35.200 --> 16:38.240
wearing makeup for fashion,
and they'd grow out of it an' that.

16:38.320 --> 16:41.480
-What's your point?
-Well, it's all got a bit serious.

16:41.560 --> 16:44.160
No one just dresses up as a bird
for a laugh anymore.

16:44.240 --> 16:46.000
Good. It was never that funny.

16:47.960 --> 16:49.200
[church bells toll]

16:55.120 --> 16:56.640
Uh... my dad died.

16:57.560 --> 16:58.400
Uh...

16:59.040 --> 17:00.120
Oh, Tony.

17:01.080 --> 17:02.640
-I'm so sorry.
-Cheers.

17:05.680 --> 17:08.640
-I'm glad you got to see so much of him.
-Mm.

17:10.760 --> 17:11.760
Such a good son.

17:11.840 --> 17:13.280
Oh... don't.

17:14.560 --> 17:15.440
[chuckles wryly]

17:17.440 --> 17:21.400
I love the fact... you said something nice
about me 'cause you know

17:21.920 --> 17:25.520
-the guilt will be kicking in about now.
-No, no. No, no.

17:27.560 --> 17:29.160
-[chuckles]
-You're a good boy.

17:29.240 --> 17:31.240
[gentle instrumental music plays]

17:38.080 --> 17:39.240
[doorbell rings]

17:41.520 --> 17:42.360
Hi.

17:42.600 --> 17:44.040
Um... Roxy's not here.

17:44.480 --> 17:46.160
Oh, I... Postcard.

17:49.360 --> 17:51.480
"Sorry about your dad. Pat." [chuckles]

17:52.840 --> 17:54.760
-[voice breaking] Cheers.
-Oh, mate.

17:54.840 --> 17:59.080
No, it's not... my dad dying.
It's kindness I have a problem with.

17:59.560 --> 18:00.560
Towards me, I mean.

18:01.000 --> 18:02.360
I don't think I deserve it.

18:02.680 --> 18:05.120
And... sorry about all the times
I was an arsehole to you,

18:05.200 --> 18:06.520
I was just lashing out.

18:07.120 --> 18:07.960
Arsehole?

18:08.520 --> 18:09.720
I thought it was banter.

18:09.800 --> 18:10.640
[chuckles]

18:12.040 --> 18:14.560
At least you didn't ignore me.
Most people do.

18:15.880 --> 18:17.560
You even sent me a postcard once.

18:18.480 --> 18:20.040
And set me up with a prossie.

18:21.200 --> 18:22.080
Sex worker.

18:22.400 --> 18:24.160
[chuckles] Wife, maybe.

18:25.800 --> 18:26.800
They're the best.

18:29.320 --> 18:30.200
Cheers.

18:31.680 --> 18:35.560
["Passing Afternoon" plays]
♪ <i>There are times that walk from you ♪</i>

18:36.600 --> 18:40.040
<i>♪ Like some passing afternoon ♪</i>

18:41.760 --> 18:46.080
<i>♪ Summer warmed the open window ♪</i>

18:46.520 --> 18:49.440
<i>♪ Of her honeymoon ♪</i>

18:50.480 --> 18:54.360
<i>♪ And she chose a yard to burn ♪</i>

18:55.120 --> 18:58.880
<i>♪ But the ground remembers her ♪</i>

19:00.640 --> 19:04.960
<i>♪ Wooden spoons</i>
<i>Her children stir her ♪</i>

19:05.360 --> 19:09.440
<i>-♪ Bougainvillea blooms ♪</i>
-[Brandy whines]

19:09.520 --> 19:13.040
♪ <i> There are things that drift away ♪</i>

19:13.480 --> 19:17.920
-[whines]
<i>-♪ Like our endless numbered days ♪</i>

19:19.440 --> 19:23.040
<i>♪ Autumn blew the quilt right off ♪</i>

19:23.120 --> 19:27.160
<i>♪ The perfect bed she made ♪</i>

19:28.000 --> 19:32.040
<i>-♪ And she's chosen to believe ♪</i>
-[Tony] Good girl.

19:32.720 --> 19:36.680
<i>-♪ In the hymns her mother sings ♪</i>
-[Brandy whimpers]

19:38.160 --> 19:42.200
<i>♪ Sometimes, with the windows closed ♪</i>

19:42.280 --> 19:45.920
<i>-♪ She'll sit and think of me ♪</i>
-[sighs heavily]

19:46.880 --> 19:50.680
♪ <i>But she'll mend his tattered clothes ♪</i>

19:51.560 --> 19:55.320
<i>♪ And they'll kiss as if they know ♪</i>

19:57.040 --> 20:00.960
<i>♪ Baby sleeps in all our bones ♪</i>

20:01.040 --> 20:07.720
<i>♪ So scared to be alone ♪</i>

20:09.920 --> 20:12.600
[vicar] <i>We meet here today</i>
<i>to honor and pay tribute</i>

20:12.680 --> 20:14.160
<i>to the life of Ray Johnson,</i>

20:14.600 --> 20:16.920
<i>and to express our love</i>
<i>and admiration for him.</i>

20:18.000 --> 20:19.760
<i>Also to try to bring some comfort</i>

20:19.840 --> 20:22.880
to those of his family and friends
who are here and grieving.

20:23.400 --> 20:25.120
Today is also a day for memories.

20:26.160 --> 20:27.360
I didn't know Ray well,

20:27.440 --> 20:30.520
but someone who did
is his beloved son Tony,

20:30.600 --> 20:33.760
who would like to share
some personal thoughts with you. Tony.

20:47.600 --> 20:49.560
Dad was born in 1939.

20:50.880 --> 20:52.360
Uh... He used to say...

20:53.120 --> 20:55.880
he was such an ugly baby
that Hitler declared war.

20:57.760 --> 20:59.520
He was such an easygoing man.

20:59.600 --> 21:03.360
You could say he had no big ambition,
he worked hard,

21:03.960 --> 21:05.040
enjoyed a drink,

21:06.080 --> 21:09.120
fell in love, got married, had a kid,

21:10.120 --> 21:12.760
did all the things he had to do
to provide

21:13.520 --> 21:15.600
and live an average life, I guess.

21:16.720 --> 21:17.800
When Mum died...

21:18.880 --> 21:21.320
[sighs]
...who he loved more than anything,

21:21.400 --> 21:22.480
I'd never seen...

21:23.240 --> 21:24.400
such a lovely pair.

21:25.600 --> 21:28.160
I think that's where
I got that beautiful dream from,

21:28.240 --> 21:31.320
that you could
bump into the perfect soulmate

21:32.040 --> 21:34.520
on this planet
of seven or eight billion people.

21:35.800 --> 21:36.640
Anyway,

21:37.720 --> 21:39.320
when Mum died, he was broken.

21:39.520 --> 21:42.040
Uh... But he even did that alone.

21:42.560 --> 21:43.680
He was old school.

21:44.480 --> 21:46.000
Just because you're unhappy

21:46.080 --> 21:48.800
doesn't mean
you have to make everyone else miserable.

21:50.160 --> 21:51.920
The opposite to my approach.

21:54.560 --> 21:55.560
He coped.

21:56.800 --> 21:58.400
Until he couldn't anymore. Uh...

21:58.600 --> 22:01.080
And that's where... Emma came in.

22:02.800 --> 22:04.920
Thank you for looking after him.

22:05.000 --> 22:07.200
He, uh... He loved you.

22:11.600 --> 22:12.640
I can see why.

22:13.400 --> 22:15.440
[mournful instrumental music plays]

22:19.080 --> 22:20.840
[Tony] Thank you. Cheers.
Thanks for coming.

22:20.920 --> 22:23.560
Thanks. Cheers. Thank you. Cheers.

22:23.640 --> 22:24.920
Bye-bye. Thanks.

22:26.360 --> 22:28.760
Yeah. Good, yeah. Cheers.
Thanks for coming.

22:28.840 --> 22:30.480
Thank you. Cheers. See you soon.

22:31.520 --> 22:34.880
Bye-bye. See you later. Cheers, man.
Thanks for coming, Kath.

22:41.560 --> 22:42.400
So...?

22:44.040 --> 22:46.120
Well... I see you every day.

22:46.200 --> 22:48.360
It's lovely. I get a lovely feeling.

22:48.440 --> 22:51.080
Why can't it just carry on like that
and then we die?

22:52.280 --> 22:54.440
Yeah. <i>Groundhog Day.</i>

22:56.080 --> 22:58.560
It might not always be like that.
I'm... better than I was.

22:58.640 --> 23:00.320
Maybe one day I won't feel...

23:00.920 --> 23:03.400
like I'm being unfaithful
to my wife, but...

23:03.880 --> 23:05.840
I just can't... I can't promise...

23:08.520 --> 23:11.160
You know... I love this, but...

23:11.920 --> 23:13.080
it can't be any more.

23:15.000 --> 23:15.920
You know?

23:16.840 --> 23:17.720
Hm.

23:18.280 --> 23:21.920
Well, I'm sorry again... about your dad.

23:25.880 --> 23:26.720
Hello.

23:29.200 --> 23:31.240
-You OK?
-Yeah.

23:31.880 --> 23:32.720
Um...

23:32.800 --> 23:33.640
You...

23:34.680 --> 23:35.640
[chuckles softly]

23:36.520 --> 23:37.640
Thanks for everything.

24:00.680 --> 24:02.520
-[Paul] Anyone sitting here?
-No.

24:02.600 --> 24:03.880
[Paul sighs]

24:05.960 --> 24:07.680
Just needed to sit down for a bit.

24:09.280 --> 24:10.680
Can't walk for too long now.

24:11.120 --> 24:13.280
-Everything is starting to ache.
-[chuckles]

24:13.680 --> 24:15.280
Ah... I won't be long.

24:16.520 --> 24:17.840
Sit as long as you like.

24:22.520 --> 24:23.520
That your husband?

24:24.320 --> 24:25.160
Yes.

24:28.360 --> 24:30.120
I lost my wife a little while back.

24:31.440 --> 24:33.440
I'm still not over it. [exhales heavily]

24:33.760 --> 24:35.960
I mean, there's nothing special
about that, I know.

24:37.840 --> 24:39.080
I bet you feel the same.

24:40.560 --> 24:41.400
Yes.

24:44.480 --> 24:48.520
"In three words, I can sum up
everything I've learned about life.

24:50.360 --> 24:51.520
It goes on."

24:53.080 --> 24:54.120
Robert Frost.

24:54.920 --> 24:56.600
-Yes!
-Wonderful.

25:01.320 --> 25:02.160
Yes.

25:03.240 --> 25:04.280
Life goes on.

25:04.680 --> 25:06.240
It's not as good... [chuckles]

25:09.120 --> 25:10.240
...but there you go.

25:11.600 --> 25:13.320
["Silence" by Don Diablo plays]

25:13.400 --> 25:16.480
♪ <i>Heard you in the distance ♪</i>

25:17.480 --> 25:19.840
<i>♪ A storm on the scope ♪</i>

25:22.120 --> 25:25.840
<i>♪ Almighty thunder coming for me</i>
<i>I hoped ♪</i>

25:29.600 --> 25:31.960
<i>♪ Rolled over the horizon ♪</i>

25:33.920 --> 25:36.040
<i>♪ Swept up it all ♪</i>

25:38.080 --> 25:42.880
<i>♪ Batten the hatches</i>
<i>And teardrops and branches ♪</i>

25:44.960 --> 25:48.560
<i>♪ But I hear the silence now ♪</i>

25:49.280 --> 25:51.640
<i>♪ Right in my core ♪</i>

25:53.120 --> 25:56.560
<i>♪ I never heard silence ♪</i>

25:57.400 --> 25:59.840
<i>♪ Like this before ♪</i>

26:01.280 --> 26:04.680
<i>♪ Yeah, I hear the silence now ♪</i>

26:05.560 --> 26:08.320
<i>♪ From wall to wall ♪</i>

26:09.560 --> 26:12.680
<i>♪ Never heard silence ♪</i>

26:13.680 --> 26:16.920
<i>♪ Like this before ♪</i>

26:17.720 --> 26:19.200
[lead jangling]

26:20.600 --> 26:23.560
♪<i> Plane flies so high ♪</i>

26:23.920 --> 26:26.960
<i>♪ Can't be seen or heard ♪</i>

26:28.040 --> 26:30.400
<i>♪ Looking down on the hills ♪</i>

26:32.280 --> 26:35.600
<i>♪ Looking down on all the birds ♪</i>

26:37.320 --> 26:38.760
[Lisa] <i>Good night, gorgeous.</i>

26:40.240 --> 26:41.240
<i>Say it back.</i>

26:42.760 --> 26:44.760
<i>You gotta say it back, or I won't sleep.</i>

26:46.480 --> 26:47.440
Good night.

26:48.840 --> 26:49.840
<i>You said it?</i>

26:51.480 --> 26:52.320
Yeah.

26:53.720 --> 26:56.280
<i>Good. Now I can sleep.</i>

26:58.520 --> 27:01.920
<i>-♪ But I hear the silence now ♪</i>
<i>-</i>[sobbing]

27:02.760 --> 27:05.440
<i>♪ From wall to wall ♪</i>

27:06.040 --> 27:09.640
<i>-</i>[Brandy whimpers]
-<i>♪ Never heard silence ♪</i>

27:10.280 --> 27:14.440
-[sniffles, sighs]
-<i>♪ Like this before ♪</i>

27:14.520 --> 27:15.600
[pills rattle]

27:26.600 --> 27:29.360
-[sniffles]
-[Brandy whines, pants]

27:37.280 --> 27:38.480
[music intensifies]

27:44.880 --> 27:46.360
[whimpers, barks]

27:50.320 --> 27:52.240
[Brandy whines, yowls]

27:57.520 --> 27:58.680
[doorbell rings]

28:12.560 --> 28:13.400
Hi.

28:14.040 --> 28:15.400
I'll take <i>Groundhog Day.</i>

28:19.800 --> 28:22.240
["The Only Thing" by Sufjan Stevens plays]

28:28.760 --> 28:35.240
<i>♪ The only thing that keeps me</i>
<i>From driving this car ♪</i>

28:37.920 --> 28:44.040
<i>♪ Half-light, jack knife</i>
<i>Into the canyon at night ♪</i>

28:47.040 --> 28:49.960
<i>♪ Signs and wonders ♪</i>

28:50.040 --> 28:53.400
<i>♪ Perseus aligned with the skull ♪</i>

28:56.040 --> 28:58.680
<i>♪ Slain Medusa ♪</i>

28:59.040 --> 29:02.040
<i>♪ Pegasus alight from us all ♪</i>

29:04.640 --> 29:08.040
<i>♪ Do I care if I survive this? ♪</i>

29:08.120 --> 29:11.560
<i>♪ Bury the dead where they're found ♪</i>

29:13.560 --> 29:16.640
<i>♪ In a veil of great surprises ♪</i>

29:16.720 --> 29:19.960
<i>♪ I wonder did you love me at all? ♪</i>
